dt: {bc}any of a widely distributed order (Pseudoscorpionida synonym Pseudoscorpiones) of tiny arachnids that have no caudal stinger and feed on tiny invertebrates (such as insects and mites)

et: New Latin {it}Pseudoscorpiones{/it}, from {it}pseud-{/it} + Latin {it}scorpion-, scorpio{/it} scorpion
shortdef: any of a widely distributed order (Pseudoscorpionida synonym Pseudoscorpiones) of tiny arachnids that have no caudal stinger and feed on tiny invertebrates (such as insects and mites)
